RACE.RACE_TEXT: KEENELAND RACE 1 7F Dirt CR: 98. Claiming Purse 56000. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Weight, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of Two Races Since February 16 Allowed 3 lbs. A Race Since Then Allowed 5 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000 (Races Where Entered For $20,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: AMERICAN PURE broke a step slow, laid off of the pace two wide, gained between horses in upper stretch to be right behind the top pair at the furlong grounds, altered course inwardly for a rail seam, bid entering the final sixteenth, and edged ahead. BEAVER HAT tracked two wide and between horse, split the leaders entering the lane to offer a bid, struck the front outside of the furlong grounds, but met an inner rival's bid at the sixteenth pole, and got outkicked. PURE PANIC prompted the pace outside of the leader from the four path, vied in the two path around the turn, led turning for home, but was headed by an inner bidder nearing the furlong grounds, and kept on. SURF AND TURF chased along the inside while under moderate coaxing, then improved position between horses in the final sixteenth. MASAI MAN pursued from midpack three wide, chased between horses around the turn, but failed to keep pace with the top flight in upper stretch. PICASSO laid off of the pace four wide, inched closer around the turn, but tired in upper stretch, and gave way while hanging on his left lead. SEA TO SUCCESS set the pace inside of a vying rival into the turn, but was headed approaching the five sixteenths pole, and weakened. RICOCHET was outrun and eased through the final furlong.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: SINFILTRE showed the way unencumbered in the two to three paths, remained well in hand along the inside around the final turn as a pair of foes gave chase, shook away from them in upper stretch, and lasted safely to the wire. ELLE EST FORTE tracked in the three path, inched closer around the final bend to claim place at the five sixteenths pole, but failed to keep pace with the leader in upper stretch while hanging on her left lead, changed over in midstretch while chasing, and kept on to narrow the margin late. I'M SO SORRY bumped an outer rival leaving the gates, stalked from the two path as the leader's closest pursuer, but was outmoved for that title turning for home, then chased along the inside through the lane while holding show. KISS YOU LATER (IRE) nudged the inner half of the gate before taking a bump from an inner rival at the start, was last away in the process, tracked from midpack two wide, was urged to gain around the far turn, tipped to the four path in upper stretch with multiple lengths to find, but lacked the needed kick to offer a bid. CECILITA saved ground off of the pace, and faded. LIVY B rated at the rear two wide, took the final two turns in three path, and failed to rally. LUMINIST trailed along the inside, and was outrun.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: HOCUS took a light brush from an inner rival at the start, rushed to the fore soon after, cleared leaving the nine sixteenths pole, showed the way with a wide margin while well in hand around the turn, then held sway under driving pressure. RACE.RACE_TEXT: KEENELAND RACE 4 1M Turf CR: 98. Allowance Purse 140000. Weight, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of $66,000 At A Mile Or Over On The Turf In 2023 Allowed 3 lbs. Non-winners Of Two Races At A Mile Or Over On The Turf Since September 1 Allowed 5 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $80,000 Or Less N ot Considered In Allowances). In the event that this race is taken off the turf it will be contested at One Mile on the main track. (Rail at 20 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GAM'S MISSION trailed along the inside, sat reserved in the two path around the far turn, shifted out to the five path entering the lane, rallied while tucking to the four path in upper stretch, sustained a bid in the final furlong, and forged an advantage late. BUBBLE ROCK set a clear pace, remained in hand as a pair of foes closed in around the far turn, shook away from them under confident handling in upper stretch, came under a drive leaving the furlong grounds as an outer GAM'S MISSION loomed a danger, and was bested by that foe in the late stages. LADY HIDEAWAY settled off of the pace along the inside, tipped to the three path entering the lane, pursued between horses while hanging on his left lead in upper stretch, but was outkicked approaching the furlong grounds, sustained stride thereafter, and gained show late. FREEDOM SPEAKS tracked from the three path, ranged up around the far turn, gained place nearing the lane, but only managed to chase the leader through upper stretch while hanging on her left lead, changed over at the three sixteenths pole, but got outkicked at the furlong grounds, tired, and lost show in the closing stages. HENRIETTA TOPHAM laid off of the pace two wide, was urged along around the far turn, but got outkicked by an outer rival while spinning into the lane in the four path, and lacked a rally. BREEZE RIDER bobbled slightly while breaking on top, stalked the clear leader from the two path, inched closer along with an outer rival around the far turn, but weakened entering the lane.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: SAUDI CROWN stalked three wide, ranged up outside of the leader and from the three path around the turn, chased that foe in upper stretch, but quickly kicked past him at the furlong grounds, and drew off with good energy. RACE.FOOTNOTES: GASLIGHT DANCER bumped with an outer rival at the start, tracked in midpack along the inside, inched closer in the two path around the turn, took aim outside of the leaders from the five path in upper stretch, bid approaching midstretch, led at the furlong grounds, and drove clear.
